<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-28T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-28T22:00:00-05:00" n="977" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d977">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 LCC/13: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-28T23:00:00-04:00">January 28,
                                1944—11 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>711. Embassy’s 729, January 27, 8 p.m. Department’s idea is that at this
                        stage the enlarged Committee will evolve over-all propaganda policy plans.
                        These plans will remain in effect, if approved by higher authority, until
                        changed by the Committee. They will govern the preparation of the weekly
                        directives and be binding upon the OWI, PWE and appropriate Russian agencies
                        unless or until modified.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>